===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# One who willingly accepts being put to death for adhering openly to one's religious beliefs; notably, [[saint]]s canonized after martyrdom.
#: ''Saint Stephen was the first Christian '''martyr'''''.
<!-- maybe somebody can find a way to include women without twice using "he or she"? -->
# {{by extension}} One who [[sacrifice]]s his or her life, station, or what is of great value to him or her, for the sake of principle or to sustain a cause.
# (''with a prepositional phrase of cause'') One who [[suffer]]s greatly and/or constantly, even involuntarily.
#: ''Stan is a '''martyr''' to arthritis, Chris a '''martyr''' to Stan's endless moaning about it.

